#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn28.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn28.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 28 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 28 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Sāriputtavagga "
msgstr "1. With Sāriputta "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn28.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Sucimukhīsutta "
msgstr "10. With Sucimukhī "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn28.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

msgctxt "sn28.10:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahe piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then he robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms. "

#. VAR: kuṭṭamūlaṃ → kuḍḍamūlaṃ (bj, s1-3, km) | kuḍḍaṃ (si, pts1)
msgctxt "sn28.10:1.3"
msgid "Rājagahe sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ aññataraṃ kuṭṭamūlaṃ nissāya paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "After wandering indiscriminately for alms-food in Rājagaha, he ate his alms-food by a wall. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho sucimukhī paribbājikā yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Sucimukhī went up to Venerable Sāriputta and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.239, sc2
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, samaṇa, adhomukho bhuñjasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Ascetic, do you eat facing downwards?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.2"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, adhomukho bhuñjāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“No, sister.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: ubbhamukho → uddhaṃmukho (bj)
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, samaṇa, ubbhamukho bhuñjasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Well then, do you eat facing upwards?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.4"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, ubbhamukho bhuñjāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“No, sister.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.5"
msgid "“Tena hi, samaṇa, disāmukho bhuñjasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Well then, do you eat facing the cardinal directions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.6"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, disāmukho bhuñjāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“No, sister.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.7"
msgid "“Tena hi, samaṇa, vidisāmukho bhuñjasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Well then, do you eat facing the intermediate directions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:2.8"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, vidisāmukho bhuñjāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“No, sister.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn28.10:3.1"
msgid "“‘Kiṃ nu, samaṇa, adhomukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, adhomukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "“When asked if you eat facing all these directions, you answer ‘no, sister’. "

msgctxt "sn28.10:3.2"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samaṇa, ubbhamukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, ubbhamukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn28.10:3.3"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samaṇa, disāmukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, disāmukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn28.10:3.4"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samaṇa, vidisāmukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, vidisāmukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn28.10:4.1"
msgid "Kathañcarahi, samaṇa, bhuñjasī”ti? "
msgstr "How exactly do you eat, ascetic?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn28.10:4.2"
msgid "“Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā vatthuvijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘adhomukhā bhuñjantī’ti. "
msgstr "“Sister, those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by geomancy—an unworthy branch of knowledge, a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing downwards. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:4.3"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā nakkhattavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘ubbhamukhā bhuñjantī’ti. "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by astrology—an unworthy branch of knowledge, a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing upwards. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogāya → … pahinagamanānuyogā (bj) | … pahiṇagamanānuyogā (s1-3, km) | … pahīṇagamanānuyogā (pts1) | … pahiṇagamanānuyogena (?)
msgctxt "sn28.10:4.4"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘disāmukhā bhuñjantī’ti. "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by running errands and messages—a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing the cardinal directions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn28.10:4.5"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā aṅgavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘vidisāmukhā bhuñjantī’ti. "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by palmistry—an unworthy branch of knowledge, a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing the intermediate directions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn28.10:5.1"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, bhagini, na vatthuvijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi, na nakkhattavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi, na dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi, na aṅgavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi. "
msgstr "I don’t earn a living by any of these means. "

msgctxt "sn28.10:5.2"
msgid "Dhammena bhikkhaṃ pariyesāmi; "
msgstr "I seek alms in a principled manner, "

msgctxt "sn28.10:5.3"
msgid "dhammena bhikkhaṃ pariyesitvā bhuñjāmī”ti. "
msgstr "and I eat it in a principled manner.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.240, sc6
msgctxt "sn28.10:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho sucimukhī paribbājikā rājagahe rathiyāya rathiyaṃ, siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamārocesi: "
msgstr "Then Sucimukhī the wanderer went around Rājagaha from street to street, from square to square, and announced: "

msgctxt "sn28.10:6.2"
msgid "“dhammikaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā āhāraṃ āhārenti; "
msgstr "“The Sakyan ascetics eat food in a principled manner! "

#. VAR: anavajjaṃ → anavajjena (mr)
msgctxt "sn28.10:6.3"
msgid "anavajjaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā āhāraṃ āhārenti. "
msgstr "The Sakyan ascetics eat food blamelessly! "

msgctxt "sn28.10:6.4"
msgid "Detha samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ piṇḍan”ti. "
msgstr "Give almsfood to the Sakyan ascetics!” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn28.10:6.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn28.10:6.6"
msgid "Sāriputtavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.1"
msgid "Vivekajaṃ avitakkaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.2"
msgid "pīti upekkhā catutthakaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.3"
msgid "Ākāsañceva viññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.4"
msgid "ākiñcaṃ nevasaññinā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.5"
msgid "Nirodho navamo vutto, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.6"
msgid "dasamaṃ sūcimukhī cāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn28.10:7.7"
msgid "Sāriputtasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Sāriputta are complete."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
